---
title: POPl 2017 Liveblog Index
author: Frédéric Bour
abstract: All the liveblogs
---

Welcome to the unofficial [POPL 2017](http://popl17.sigplan.org)
liveblog!  This is a resource intended to capture attendees notes
across the [hundreds of talks](http://popl17.sigplan.org/program/program-POPL-2017) that will be given at POPL 2017 in Paris, France.
Any attendee of the conference is welcome to contribute their notes here, and
we will aggregate them after the event into an archive.

The following events/days are being liveblogged:

* **[CPP - Jan 16](CPP-16)** - *[homepage](http://popl17.sigplan.org/track/CPP-2017)*, *[issues](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3ACPP)*
* **[CPP - Jan 17](CPP-17)** - *[homepage](http://popl17.sigplan.org/track/CPP-2017)*, *[issues](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3ACPP)*
* **[POPL main conference - Jan 18](POPL)** - *[homepage](http://popl17.sigplan.org)*, *[issues](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3APOPL)*
* **[POPL main conference - Jan 19](POPL)** - *[homepage](http://popl17.sigplan.org)*, *[issues](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3APOPL)*
* **[POPL main conference - Jan 20](POPL)** - *[homepage](http://popl17.sigplan.org)*, *[issues](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3APOPL)*
* **[CoqPL](CoqPL)** - *[homepage](http://popl17.sigplan.org/track/main)*, *[issues](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3ACoqPL)*

Some useful resources:
* Data is a Git repo at <https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog>; [PRs](https://help.github.com/articles/creating-a-pull-request/) welcome!
* POPL preprints: <https://github.com/gasche/popl2017-papers>
* Conference website: <http://www.sigplan.org/Conferences/POPL>

Site Info:
* It is served via an OCaml [MirageOS](https://mirage.io) [unikernel](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unikernel) running on [Docker Cloud](http://cloud.docker.com).
* The blog software is the [Canopy](https://github.com/engil/canopy) system built by [Enguerrand Decorne](https://github.com/Engil) during an internship at [OCaml Labs](http://ocaml.io) in Cambridge.
* The scripts for generating the Git templates are available [here](https://github.com/ocamllabs/popl2017-blog/tree/code)

